notes.note:
Hey Steve, good news, I spoke a little more about the transmission fluid replacement invoices with my Claims Manager. He said that in this case, because Hyundai recommends the fluid be replaced every 96,000 km's, and the customer has not driven 96,000 km's since they purchased the vehicle, we will not need maintenance receipts to proceed with the claim. That being said, we are able to move forward with the claim for the transmission replacement. Please be advised, the customer is responsible for any diagnostic fees, fluids, filters, and shop supplies, as well as a $100 deductible + tax. Additionally, the customer has a $5000 single claim limit, less their deductible of $100 for a total single claim limit of $4900. The payout is as follows:
